MOD_OSMOD_MP_MULTIPIN="Additional pins"
MOD_OSMOD_MP_PINS="Pins"
MOD_OSMOD_MP_PINS_DESC="Create pins: #pin1{ (lat,lon), #custompin1, {#popup1, click} };<ul><li>(lat,lon) - <i>Koordinates: latitude & longitude</i></li><li>#custompin1 - <i>OPTIONAL custom pin</i></li><li>{#popup, click} - <i>OPTIONAL popup: Show by 'click' or 'always'</i></li></ul>Definions begin always with # and end with ;. Parameters are inside {}. Parameters can be combined with {}. Custom pins and popups  are defined by the text boxes below. Minimal example: #pin1{(100,50.4),,};"
MOD_OSMOD_MP_CUSTOMS="Benutzerdefinierte Pins"
MOD_OSMOD_MP_CUSTOMS_DESC="#customStyle1{"pinimage", (wxh), "shadowimage", (wxh), (wxh), (wxh)};<ul><li>"pinimage" - <i>Pin image file</i></li><li>(wxh) - <i>Dimensions of the picture in px zB: 24x24</i></li><li>"shadowimage" - <i>Shadow image file</i></li><li>(wxh) - <i>Dimensions of the picture in px zB: 24x24</i></li><li>(wxh) - <i>Where the pin hits the map. 0x0 ist the top-left corner. Example: 12x24</i></li><li>(wxh) - <i>Where the popup hits the pin. 0x0 ist the pin point. Example: 0x-24</i></li></ul>Definions begin always with # and end with ;. Parameters are inside {}."
MOD_OSMOD_MP_POPUPS="Popups"
MOD_OSMOD_MP_POPUPS_DESC="popup contents: #popup1{bla &lt;b&gt;bla&lt;/b&gt; bla};<br><br>Definions begin always with # and end with ;. Parameters are inside {}. HTML-Code is allowed."

